resources.data_redundancy_tooltip_content_1:
Locally Redundant Storage (LRS)

Makes multiple synchronous copies of your data within a single datacenter

Zone Redundant Storage (ZRS)

Stores three copies of data across multiple datacenters within or across regions. For block blobs only.

Geographically Redundant Storage (GRS)

Same as LRS, plus multiple asynchronous copies to a second datacenter hundreds of miles away.

Read-Access Geographically Redundant Storage (RA-GRS)

Same as GRS, plus read access to the secondary datacenter.

Learn more
resources.sync_servers_footnote: NOTE: One sync server is free per storage sync service. Sync uses file operations to sync your data to the cloud and sync servers. You will be additionally billed for any operations that are generated in the sync process.
